reviews.reviewTitle: You wont want to be without one after you use it
reviews.reviewText: I had to buy another set of these as when I sold my car the buyer wanted to keep the first lot. These ones are as large as your front seat and are of a nice quality material and the elasticated pockets look like they will last the abuse my kids will give them. Attaching them to the seat is easy with 2 adjustable straps with a klik-loks. You can keep packing them long after you think they'd be full.With a youngster on board you can put one on the back of the seat for their books/games and one facing forwards next to them with drinks and wipes etc. When Im on a journey on my own I clip one to the front of the passenger seat facing forwards to keep all the stuff in that rattles around that you may need when theres no spare pair of hands to pass you stuff - Ive yet to ask the wife sit in the back so I can keep it there :)Since having these I no longer have to take up the space in the boot and the dog seems to be a lot more relaxedIf you like my feedback please click it as useful as it is encouraging to write more of them
